To create a Paper plugin that listens to PlayerJoinEvent and sends a custom welcome message, follow these steps:





Create a new plugin project: Use the Paper API plugin template to create a new plugin project. This will set up the basic structure and dependencies for your plugin.


Implement the PlayerJoinEvent listener: In your plugin's main class, create a method that will be called when a PlayerJoinEvent occurs.




JAVA
Copy
@EventHandler
public void onPlayerJoin(PlayerJoinEvent event) {
    Player player = event.getPlayer();
    player.sendMessage(ChatColor.GREEN + "Welcome to the server!");
}





Register the plugin: In the onEnable method of your plugin's main class, register the PlayerJoinEvent listener.




JAVA
Copy
@Override
public void onEnable() {
    getServer().getPluginManager().registerEvents(this, getServer());
}




Now, when a player joins the server, they will receive a custom welcome message. You can customize the message to fit your needs.

